Lee Chong Wei is a retired professional badminton player from Malaysia who is widely regarded as one of the greatest badminton players of all time. He was born on October 21, 1982, in Bagan Serai, Perak, Malaysia. Lee won a record 12 Malaysian Open titles and was the World No. 1 badminton player for a total of 199 weeks. He won three silver medals in the men's singles event at the Olympic Games (2008, 2012, 2016) and also won three silver and one bronze medal at the World Championships. After a long and successful career, Lee retired from professional badminton in 2019.